{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"36a780d9-6169-45e1-9eec-3f3ee253f68b","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"055b468d-a86a-4797-bf32-712da6ef51a5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"CFDB:91905:1515792:186AA2B:69EC1550"},"id":"cf817c59-3e51-4393-be45-6c4692268dfe","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:13:56.682Z","parentId":"660fa737-2520-454d-9d5d-1666c821623c"}
